# WhatsApp Messaging Agent

**A LangGraph agent that scans your WhatsApp Web inbox, reads unread conversations, generates contextual AI replies, sends them, and emails an HTML report.**

The agent signs into **Gmail** with `EMAIL` and `PASSWORD` from `.env`. During inbox scan it opens [web.whatsapp.com](https://web.whatsapp.com/) and processes **unread** chats only ŌĆö contacts with unread messages get extracted conversation context, Groq AI analysis, replies through WhatsApp Web, screenshots after each send, and an HTML report with the message/reply log.

## Quick start

```bash
./setup.sh
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env: GROQ_API_KEY, EMAIL, PASSWORD, optional Gmail SMTP for email reports
./start.sh both
```

Open **http://localhost:5173** and click **Start Agent**.

### First-time browser login

Set in `.env`:

```env
EMAIL=your.email@gmail.com
PASSWORD=your_gmail_password
BROWSER_HEADLESS=false
```

Run the agent once. Playwright signs into Gmail (login step). WhatsApp Web opens during inbox scan ŌĆö scan QR if prompted. The session is saved to `./data/whatsapp_session.json` for reuse.

## Workflow

```
Gmail login (EMAIL/PASSWORD) ŌåÆ WhatsApp Web (inbox scan) ŌåÆ Unread chats only ŌåÆ Extract conversations
  ŌåÆ Analyze sentiment ŌåÆ Select reply targets ŌåÆ Generate contextual AI replies
  ŌåÆ Send on WhatsApp + screenshot ŌåÆ HTML report ŌåÆ PDF (optional) ŌåÆ Email
```

## Environment variables

| Variable | Default | Purpose |
|----------|---------|---------|
| `GROQ_API_KEY` | ŌĆö | **Required** ŌĆö LLM for analysis and replies |
| `EMAIL` | ŌĆö | **Required** ŌĆö Gmail address for browser login |
| `PASSWORD` | ŌĆö | **Required** ŌĆö Gmail password for browser login |
| `WHATSAPP_SESSION_PATH` | `./data/whatsapp_session.json` | Saved browser session |
| `MAX_CHATS_TO_PROCESS` | `5` | Max unread chats to open per run |
| `MAX_MESSAGES_PER_CHAT` | `20` | Recent inbound messages per chat |
| `MAX_REPLIES_PER_RUN` | `5` | Max AI replies per run |
| `REPLY_ONLY_UNREAD_CHATS` | `true` | Reply only to chats with unread messages |
| `CONTACT_FILTER` | ŌĆö | Optional name filter (partial match) |
| `ENABLE_MESSAGE_REPLIES` | `false` | Send replies via WhatsApp Web |
| `BROWSER_HEADLESS` | `true` | Set `false` for QR login |
| `KEEP_BROWSER_OPEN` | `true` | Reuse browser from login through send |

See `.env.example` for the full list.

## Project structure

```
src/agent/
  graph.py              # LangGraph workflow
  config.py             # Environment config
  workflow_executor.py  # Step handlers
  custom_tools/
    browser_tools.py    # WhatsApp Web session
    whatsapp_tools.py   # Inbox scan, read, send, screenshots
frontend/               # React agent dashboard
```

## Run commands

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `./start.sh both` | LangGraph server + React UI |
| `./start.sh server` | LangGraph API only |
| `./start.sh ui` | Frontend only |

